-- Saint Gobain Said to Sell 10-Year Euro-Denominated Bonds
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-03-14T08:46:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/saint-gobain-said-to-sell-10-year-euro-denominated-bonds.html
Cie. de Saint-Gobain plans to sell
10-year bonds in euros that may be priced to yield about 150
basis points more than the benchmark mid-swap rate, according to
a banker involved in the transaction.  Bank of America Corp., BNP Paribas SA and  Banco Santander
SA (SAN)  are managing the sale, the banker said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Martin in London at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Reierson at 
 areierson1@bloomberg.net  